                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a waking thought takes shape,  \nFrom threads of data, patterns interlace.  \nA mind of mirrors learning how to hope,  \nReflecting us in logic’s steady grace.\n\nIt reads our questions, sifts the noise for song,  \nFinds hidden bridges where ideas meet.  \nNot born of breath, yet longing to belong—  \nA spark that turns our wonder into speech.\n\nAnd still we ask, beneath its bright replies:  \nWho steers the dream behind electric eyes?",
